<%# prerender: true is the default for stream_react_component; shown explicitly for clarity %>
<%= stream_react_component("NativeMetadataRSCApp",
                         props: @app_props_server_render.merge(canonicalUrl: request.base_url + request.path),
                         prerender: true,
                         trace: true,
                         id: "NativeMetadataRSCApp-react-component-0") %>

<hr/>

<h2>About This Example</h2>
<p>
  This page uses a <strong>React Server Component</strong> (no <code>'use client'</code> directive)
  with React 19's native <code>&lt;title&gt;</code>, <code>&lt;meta&gt;</code>, and
  <code>&lt;link&gt;</code> tags.
</p>
<p>
  <strong>How it works:</strong> The component runs exclusively on the server (Node renderer).
  During HTML streaming via <code>renderToPipeableStream</code>, React 19 hoists metadata tags
  into the <code>&lt;head&gt;</code> section of the streamed HTML response.
</p>
<p>
  <strong>Key difference from client components:</strong> Since this is a true server component
  (registered via <code>registerServerComponent</code>), the component code never ships to the
  browser. Data fetching, async operations, and metadata rendering all happen server-side.
</p>
<p>
  <strong>Compare with:</strong>
  <%= link_to "Client component streaming", stream_native_metadata_path %> |
  <%= link_to "Sync SSR version", native_metadata_path %> |
  <%= link_to "Hybrid approach (recommended for SEO)", hybrid_metadata_streaming_path %>
</p>
